headline: 3 High-Yield Stocks Beating the Market Slump That You Can Still Buy Hand Over Fist
summary: Shares of Calgary-based energy company Enbridge (NYSE: ENB) are up roughly 6% year to date while the S&P 500 has sunk into a correction.  Enbridge operates an extensive network of pipelines that transport oil, natural gas, and natural gas liquids in Canada and the U.S. It owns the largest gas utility in North America, serving around 7 million customers in Ohio, Ontario, North Carolina, and Utah.  Income investors should like Enbridge's forward dividend yield of 5.91%.
